# .env.example
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variable template for the Feedback Analysis System.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file and rename the copy to ".env"
#      (on Mac/Linux: cp .env.example .env)
#   2. Fill in your actual values in the .env file.
#   3. The .env file is listed in .gitignore — it will NOT be committed to Git.
#      Never share or commit your actual .env file.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Groq API Key (required for cloud LLM inference) ───────────────────────────
# Get your free API key at: https://console.groq.com
# The key looks like: gsk_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# ── Ollama settings (optional — only needed if using local inference) ──────────
# If you are running Ollama on a non-default port or a remote host, change this.
# Leave blank or omit to use the default: http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
